{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Kids should learn right from wrong from their parents and communities/churches. What is lawful isn't always right \\(for example: adultery\\). I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There have been [no positive consequences](http://fileserver.idpc.net/library/Shadow%20Report_FINAL_ENGLISH.pdf) as a result of the war on drugs. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs means that they are taken, and disposed of, more safely and cautiously than in the current environment.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The "[27 club](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/27_Club)" is an infamous list of artists who died from overdosing on drugs at the age of 27. That\'s why drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The increased tax revenue could enable increased government spending, which [results in more jobs](https://www.americanprogress.org/issues/economy/reports/2011/09/08/10257/government-spending-can-create-jobs-and-it-has/).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'They may lose their job and thus stop contributing to society and paying taxes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Such stress might be irrational, especially when it's related to unproblematic drug use. In that case, the psychological stress is the fault of the persons irrational beliefs."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Some people may become psychologically stressed about a friend/relative coming out as gay, or an atheist as well. That doesn't mean the friend/relative did anything wrong. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalizing drugs will not automatically remove the prejudice. If people see those on drugs being violent or a nuisance to society, the prejudice will likely remain. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "But we don't make moral judgements all the time every day. We all need to stop thinking clearly and rationally every now and then, for activities including but not limited to play, fun, pleasure, love, chilling out, taking a load offâ€¦ So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A [Constitutional Amendment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eighteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution) had to be voted on for the prohibition of alcohol. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "This is an argument of the ends justifying the means. The government could generate more income by simply taking everyone's money by force - that doesn't make it a good choice. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is no way to determine in advance what the additional resources/revenue will be used for by the government. It may not be earmarked for harm reduction. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without help some conditions could [worsen](https://deserthopetreatment.com/co-occurring-disorders/going-untreated/) to the point where they're a danger to others. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegal drug dealers typically require no age verification from their clients. Legal drugs would require ID to buy thus making them harder for teens to aquire. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is perhaps a fantastic way to prevent drug abuse in children and, hopefully therefore, adults too. However, it doesn't contribute to bringing down cartels or allow healthy adults to use recreational drugs in the safest possible way."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
